snippet.textDisplay:
According to me, this was set right after blinding lights and heartless which set the mood after MDMA where he was coping with the pain by drug usage and partying. But the third single and the title track sets the overall mood which was a mixture of all the chapters of Weeknd we've seen(kinda). So after coming from Jimmy Kimmel we see how he's actually sad when he's alone. But him being dragged in the subway and then suddenly seeing him in the elevator totally normal is a sign that something supernatural happened to our Abel and he's gone and a brutal, more heartless Abel has taken his place (kind of like he's possessed) and the music is gonna be dark af. Hence no more daytime music.

Or maybe I'm just too high.
